Editor’s note: This livestream has ended. You may watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The Premier Soccer League (PSL) held a press conference on Monday at 12:00 CAT to address the violence that broke out at Moses Mabhida Stadium in Durban on Saturday. The press briefing was addressed by PSL chairperson Irvin Khoza. Violence broke out after frustrated Chiefs fans invaded the field following their teams 2-0 defeat by Free State Stars in their Nedbank Cup semi-final. READ: Soccer fans slam Kaizer Chiefs supporters for stadium rampage Spectators took their frustrations out on equipment and security personnel, leaving one security guard in serious condition in hospital, as they vented their fury at a string of poor performances under coach Steve  Komphela. Two people who were arrested in connection with the violence at the stadium are appearing in the Durban Magistrate's Court on Monday. Komphela resigned as Chiefs coach immediately after the game after three years at the helm of Amakhosi. Police used teargas to disperse the pitch invaders after some spectators starrted fires in the stadium. eNCA